sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant C as Caller / Driver
  participant E as Engine
  participant Q as Ready set
  participant P as Worker pool
  participant H as Job handler
  participant EV as EventPublisher port

  C->>E: schedule*(job) → jobId
  E->>EV: JobScheduled
  C->>E: tick(now)
  E->>Q: pick due jobs (priority, nextRun, createdAt)
  loop while capacity and due jobs remain
    E->>P: acquire worker (running < concurrency)
    E->>EV: JobStarted
    P->>H: handler(ctx = jobId, attempt, signal, ...)
    alt success
      H-->>P: resolve
      E->>EV: JobCompleted
      opt recurring
        E->>Q: reschedule next occurrence
      end
    else timeout
      P->>H: signal.abort()
      E->>EV: JobTimedOut
      E->>E: apply retry policy
    else throw
      E->>E: apply retry policy
    end
    alt retry allowed
      E->>Q: requeue (nextRun = now + backoff)
      E->>EV: JobRetried
    else exhausted
      E->>E: push to dead-letter
      E->>EV: JobFailed
    end
    E->>P: release worker
  end
  E-->>C: { started }
